Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.17,0:01:47.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Now, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.11,0:01:50.95,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You have your power now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.58,0:01:58.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The last place upon which you stand \Nwill become your true home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.07,0:02:01.96,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.67,0:02:04.00,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to mess with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.45,0:02:08.53,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Do you despise humans so \Nmuch for tying you down?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:13.77,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,She'll be back if she longs to come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:20.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it ought to be more convenient for \Nyou to keep her with you in a non-human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.07,0:02:26.95,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,A human life is more brittle than that \Nof a failure born in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.73,0:02:31.05,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You all avoid me, saying that's what I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.58,0:02:35.33,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,But I hate the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.37,0:02:43.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,How absolutely endearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.17,0:02:56.52,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's so beautiful and fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:02.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.89,0:03:04.19,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What was I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.63,0:03:07.66,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.40,0:03:11.56,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like someone's shouting by my ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.11,0:03:14.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,How far should I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.37,0:03:17.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I could go on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.71,0:03:28.72,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,To where there are no people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.15,0:03:31.15,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Are you leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.77,0:03:32.84,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.84,0:03:34.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm being called.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.13,0:03:36.18,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:37.28,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.15,0:03:39.48,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:41.15,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.11,0:03:45.11,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,If it's what you want, I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.63,0:03:49.45,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,But is there nothing left \Nfor you back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.26,0:03:52.29,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:55.22,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I... What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.74,0:03:56.20,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.25,0:04:02.67,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, there is a lot \Nthat I still don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.93,0:04:11.10,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I need you with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.97,0:04:14.81,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:16.61,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.65,0:04:22.17,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Without you, it's so cold and lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:34.07,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I hate the cold, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.93,0:04:37.68,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.51,0:04:46.08,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It still feels like there's \Na fog over my brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.46,0:04:48.56,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,It's a kind of curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.53,0:04:50.70,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:53.70,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,This hide turns the wearer \Ninto a werebeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.18,0:04:56.89,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Though this hide is that of a fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.53,0:05:01.44,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,The hide of a werebeast \Nanswers to one's wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.98,0:05:04.21,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,What an awful thing he left me with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.21,0:05:06.73,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Ask me when you want to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.73,0:05:09.30,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,This certainly was mischievous of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.30,0:05:10.49,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,And he's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.92,0:05:12.20,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.79,0:05:24.13,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What if I'd gone to the other side?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.69,0:05:27.21,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop you if that's not what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.21,0:05:29.81,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Stop me even if I do want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.94,0:05:31.93,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.41,0:05:33.68,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.72,0:05:37.67,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.17,0:05:40.64,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Save Joel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.98,0:05:44.73,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.93,0:05:54.72,Magus-Flashback,Service,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't woken up all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.55,0:05:58.40,Magus-Flashback,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.55,0:06:00.81,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, get on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.35,0:06:02.09,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.09,0:06:03.37,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.29,0:06:19.34,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You are a good lock, an old lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.95,0:06:22.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I am your good oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.24,0:06:24.86,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I am your golden key.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.57,0:06:28.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Joel!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:31.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Joel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.17,0:06:32.29,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Joel!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.57,0:06:39.24,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Chise...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.97,0:06:43.17,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,So this is why you bolted out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.70,0:06:44.76,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.37,0:06:49.01,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter with that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.49,0:06:50.76,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,He's almost dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.86,0:06:55.26,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,A Leannán Sídhe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.82,0:06:57.93,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? Aren't \Nyou going to eat him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.41,0:07:00.03,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,He's your prey, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.03,0:07:01.86,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.86,0:07:04.11,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't eat him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.11,0:07:05.47,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a single drop of blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.47,0:07:07.10,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a speck of his life!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:09.40,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,A human's fate is sealed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:13.70,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,once they're haunted by a vampire, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.76,0:07:15.68,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.21,0:07:17.12,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.77,0:07:19.09,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not haunting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:24.92,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.33,0:07:28.55,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,If I go away, he might...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.55,0:07:29.48,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.90,0:07:33.59,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You've already put your hand on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.59,0:07:34.86,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.03,0:07:38.55,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No matter far you go, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.55,0:07:39.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:43.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.80,0:07:46.05,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Can you keep an eye on Mr. Joel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:48.34,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:53.99,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I don't love him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:55.81,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.57,0:08:00.96,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I don't love that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.04,0:08:03.92,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.43,0:08:05.15,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:06.05,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:09.88,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.88,0:08:18.93,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,If I loved him, we would have to\N follow through with that love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.59,0:08:35.74,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Night time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:37.74,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.80,0:08:48.90,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the grim reaper or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.90,0:08:50.95,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.95,0:08:53.13,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,My girl has been in your care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.50,0:08:56.34,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.69,0:09:01.72,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,She sure was a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.68,0:09:08.27,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:11.39,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something you can \Nhave treated at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.33,0:09:24.57,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Kind grim reaper, may I ask \Nhow much time I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.98,0:09:26.61,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,A week at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.97,0:09:28.63,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Will I suffer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:29.90,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Likely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.63,0:09:34.47,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty good, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.04,0:09:37.48,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a pretty good life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.27,0:09:42.18,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Are you not afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.97,0:09:45.38,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.38,0:09:47.85,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone fears death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.48,0:09:51.69,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something I can avoid, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.97,0:09:57.64,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,My wife passed away young.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.42,0:10:01.16,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,We were introduced to each \Nother through our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.16,0:10:05.40,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,We hadn't married for love, \Nbut still, I was devastated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.74,0:10:12.48,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,But the rose garden that my wife had \Nleft me saved me from my despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.63,0:10:16.80,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been no more \Nthan a midsummer illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.80,0:10:20.47,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,but I met a beautiful woman there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.32,0:10:23.43,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I'm content.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.72,0:10:33.45,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,That said, if I could just meet that woman\Nwith eyes like red currants once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.29,0:10:35.77,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I ask for too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:48.59,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,A fairy ointment?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:50.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,May I make some?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.16,0:10:52.09,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.50,0:10:55.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,We can rub it on his eyelids.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.78,0:10:59.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It'll let even an ordinary person\N like Mr. Joel see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.14,0:11:04.26,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,That ointment isn't meant \Nto be used on humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.79,0:11:08.56,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,The neighbors would be \Nfurious if they found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.55,0:11:13.88,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But I want him to have just one glimpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.76,0:11:17.52,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,To share just one word.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.27,0:11:20.13,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.94,0:11:23.76,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,...is what I'd like to say, but okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.68,0:11:28.10,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard you make demands before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:31.17,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,However, you'll not be pushing yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.17,0:11:31.80,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.98,0:11:33.93,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.89,0:11:40.86,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,How did you let that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.86,0:11:42.55,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.50,0:11:46.65,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You need to keep it in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.02,0:11:49.17,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help you this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.57,0:11:52.62,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I can't help, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.62,0:11:53.48,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.09,0:11:59.28,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Fairies hate being seen. Even familiars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.95,0:12:06.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias, do you think I can do it by myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:11.72,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I'd prefer that you didn't, \Nespecially given your frail body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:16.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:19.12,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Just this once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.67,0:12:28.72,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,When I use magic, I stare really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.62,0:12:34.22,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Then I can see light dancing. Playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.28,0:12:39.67,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This is what they call magic power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:43.73,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,One moment, it takes on the \Ncolor of the stars at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.17,0:12:51.45,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The next, it's blue as the sea, \Nor green as the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.18,0:12:54.67,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,At times, it whitens, like the morning sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.22,0:13:01.43,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Together, like a crib, entwined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.36,0:13:06.37,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.37,0:13:11.86,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that looks good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:16.09,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Now you have to maintain \Nit for the next five days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.40,0:13:17.06,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:19.82,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare push yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.82,0:13:22.03,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,If something happens, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.03,0:13:23.08,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:23.98,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.63,0:13:32.95,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I feel something important \Nleaving my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.17,0:13:37.29,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.26,0:13:44.50,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Is someone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.64,0:13:55.23,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,With the flowers that \Nbloom in spring water,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:14:01.19,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,from old gold coins submerged \Nwithin it, an incense is made.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.44,0:14:07.99,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,One day in the full moon, and then in each \Nof the four directions of the compass,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.41,0:14:10.99,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,it's bathed in moonlight and sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:16.66,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I have to stay with the \Nmedicine jar the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.41,0:14:19.21,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even allow myself to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.27,0:14:24.55,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Even then, there's only a 50-50 \Nchance that it'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.06,0:14:30.32,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.81,0:14:36.78,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you do for others, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.93,0:14:47.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that I want people who \Nsmiled at me to keep smiling for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:54.61,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.71,0:14:59.61,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,And selfish, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.79,0:15:06.05,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,How many days has it been now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.75,0:15:08.41,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,It's the fourth day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:11.93,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:27.33,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I smell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.42,0:15:28.36,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I smell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.02,0:15:30.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There's a scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.69,0:15:32.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,A scent of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.72,0:15:35.87,Default,Whacko,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.08,0:15:39.87,Default,Whacko,0000,0000,0000,,They're up to something fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.26,0:16:03.09,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, I fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.44,0:16:12.68,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.12,0:16:14.39,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:16.39,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, it worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.18,0:16:19.28,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You just barely made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.85,0:16:29.07,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You can do with it as you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.11,0:16:34.73,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Do what's right for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.38,0:17:08.00,Magus-Internal/narrator,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Am I dreaming?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:10.84,Magus-Internal/narrator,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't even get out \Nof bed until just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.50,0:17:14.02,Magus-Internal/narrator,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I've been \Nsleeping for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.13,0:17:30.85,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I finally meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:35.33,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.51,0:17:36.53,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.02,0:17:39.86,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,It's all because you found me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.50,0:17:47.33,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault that I can't leave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.34,0:17:50.70,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.29,0:17:53.21,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.87,0:17:55.64,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you apologizing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.62,0:17:58.26,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.26,0:18:00.09,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You're scared of passing on by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.82,0:18:04.87,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.71,0:18:14.62,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for loving me, \NLeannán Sídhe, lover of poets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.24,0:18:17.21,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as if I never knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:22.78,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,You can have my life, if such an \Nold life is good enough for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:24.66,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,You can have all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.63,0:18:30.70,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,But, but.. I did nothing \Nbut take from you, Joel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.17,0:18:32.83,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I never gave you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:35.17,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Sure you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.95,0:18:42.98,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Since my wife died, my life had \Nbeen going on nothing but inertia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.31,0:18:44.68,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,But one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.52,0:18:49.23,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,just for a brief moment, our eyes met.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.43,0:18:53.14,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,They were so, so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.53,0:18:55.66,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.36,0:19:01.19,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,That, by itself, gave my life \Na push against the inertia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:19.47,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You're such an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.28,0:19:24.26,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You're making it even harder \Nfor me to leave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.06,0:19:32.85,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know where I'm going next.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:37.29,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll even get to be at my wife's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.75,0:19:42.70,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,But I will surely, surely \Ncome to your side, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.91,0:19:45.95,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I'm not alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.45,0:19:51.92,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,as long as someone's waiting for me, \NI'm not the slightest bit afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.71,0:19:58.09,Default,Fan,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to have this life of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.15,0:20:31.23,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot, I didn't even get to reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.65,0:20:35.05,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You humans really are foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.05,0:20:36.91,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,You're so selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.16,0:20:58.63,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.79,0:21:03.83,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait here until the end\Nof the world for Joel to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.49,0:21:11.05,Default,Service,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.21,0:21:20.41,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.36,0:21:27.32,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.91,0:21:29.13,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You're crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.13,0:21:30.74,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.19,0:21:33.85,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.79,0:21:35.87,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:42.37,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,But seeing you cry makes me \Nfeel a little uneasy inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.94,0:21:47.15,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I couldn't be your teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.53,0:21:48.54,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:51.76,Default,Edgelord,0000,0000,0000,,You should get some rest in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.51,0:21:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.74,0:21:54.77,Default,Whacko,0000,0000,0000,,Boo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.77,0:21:55.57,Default,Whacko,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.66,0:21:57.95,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oberon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.95,0:22:02.46,Default,Whacko,0000,0000,0000,,The fairy ointment: Eyelid Joy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:07.09,Default,Whacko,0000,0000,0000,,It's a big no-no for a human to make that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:10.54,Default,Whacko,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but can I have the rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.24,0:22:13.05,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.32,0:23:59.44,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The price of violating\Nthe taboo was far too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.91,0:24:02.37,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The girl, consumed by the \Nfestering shadows of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.37,0:24:04.71,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,is given a hand by the fae, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.50,0:24:08.72,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,These children become weaker and weaker.
